# Pagination & Sorting Infrastructure

## Key Types

| Type | Layer | Source |
|---|---|---|
| `SortOrder` | Domain | `@lib/core` — `ASC = 'asc'` / `DESC = 'desc'` |
| `BaseFilter<T>` | Domain | `@lib/core` — carries `pageIndex`, `pageSize`, `sortBy`, `sortDir`, `props` |
| `PaginatedQueryDto` | Presentation | `@lib/core` — class-validator + Swagger decorated base query DTO |

## Controller List Endpoints

Use `@Query() query: PaginatedQueryDto` — never raw `@Query('pageIndex')` / `@Query('pageSize')`.
Pass all four pagination/sort fields into `BaseFilter`:

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
@Get()
@ApiAutoPagedResponse(RoleResponseDto)
listRoles(@Query() query: PaginatedQueryDto): Promise<PagedResponse<RoleResponseDto>> {
  return this.queryBus.execute(
    new ListRolesQuery(
      new BaseFilter(undefined, query.pageIndex, query.pageSize, query.sortBy, query.sortDir),
    ),
  );
}

// ❌ BAD — raw params, no shared DTO
listRoles(
  @Query('pageIndex') pageIndex?: number,
  @Query('pageSize') pageSize?: number,
) { ... }
```

Do NOT add manual `@ApiQuery({ name: 'pageIndex', ... })` decorators — `PaginatedQueryDto` documents them automatically.

## Module-Specific Query DTOs

When a list endpoint has extra filter fields, extend `PaginatedQueryDto` — never redeclare `pageIndex`/`pageSize`:

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
export class ListOrdersRequestDto extends PaginatedQueryDto {
  @ApiPropertyOptional()
  @IsOptional()
  @IsString()
  status?: string;

  // Constrain sortBy to allowed columns
  @IsIn(['createdAt', 'totalAmount'])
  override sortBy?: string;
}

// ❌ BAD — redeclares pageIndex/pageSize
export class ListOrdersRequestDto {
  @IsOptional() pageIndex?: number;
  @IsOptional() pageSize?: number;
  @IsOptional() status?: string;
}
```

## Domain Layer — BaseFilter

`BaseFilter<T>` constructor signature (all optional, positions 4–5 are new):

```typescript
new BaseFilter(props?, pageIndex?, pageSize?, sortBy?, sortDir?)
```

All existing 3-arg call sites are unaffected.

## Infrastructure — PrismaCrudRepositoryBase

`findPaged()` resolves sort dynamically: if `filter?.sortBy` is set it builds `{ [sortBy]: sortDir ?? SortOrder.ASC }`; otherwise it falls back to the protected `defaultOrderBy()` hook — no change needed for existing repos.

## Layer Rules

- `SortOrder` lives in **domain** (`src/core/domain/models/sort-order.enum.ts`) — `BaseFilter` (domain) depends on it; domain must not import from presentation.
- `PaginatedQueryDto` lives in **presentation** (`src/core/presentation/models/paginated-query.dto.ts`) — it carries `@nestjs/swagger` and `class-validator` decorators which must not enter the domain layer.

## Do NOT Migrate

The `queue` module pagination feeds BullMQ's Redis range API — it is not `BaseFilter`-based and must stay as-is.
